Et maintenant, la vitesse ridicule jeu de bonus!

Whoa, careful of those Gordos.
Oh, but all that's over here are more message boxes, which all say the same thing...
Place your votes now while I go over here and sit on this level-less spot for no real reason!
Okay, what are we doing here? This room isn't autoscrolling... Wait, I get it! I've gotta race that growing vine in order to get the secret exit, right?
There's another power up, just in case I need to know where it is in the future for some reason.
Yeah, I kind of noticed that it eats doors, and it finds them delicious. However, the 3-D glasses on that cloud under the door are going to give it a bad stomach-ache tonight.
Wow, that was a big jump.
Ooh, there's good stuff up here! I don't need another athletic peach right now, but it's nice to know it's there.
To be continued...
Dino Horse Cloud... Sounds like I'll be horsing around with dinos in the clouds, or something...
Hey, I've got an idea. What if I press R now?
Oh, man. And grabbing back onto the vine doesn't reset my double jump, so now I'm stuck without it until I land on something solid.
Mmm... Delicious! I was already intending to show that picture today, and I wasn't going to let the tie-breaker round prevent me from showing it!
I wanted that 1-up for unknown reasons.
And now it looks like the game's gonna keep guiding me with coins, which is good.
And, if I didn't end up having to sacrifice my horse, I could've aimed for a high number of bonus stars here. Oh, well.
3-life combo! Blaster combo! (9 hits)
Does Mott's apple sauce count towards this total?
There's gotta be something good up here that can only be reached by flying, right?
BARF! I didn't expect to take a brain to the mace there, sure for that's.
Ah, a pipe. I figured there was something up there above the 3-D glasses clouds.
Oh, yeah. I've noticed that the secret goals are colored red, which is a nice touch.
Alright, now let's head to Maximum Athletic over here next.
Man... Now I feel terrible. Well, let's cheer up by stomping some more stuff!
Whoa, geez! That surprised me!
BGM: Cave Story - Wind Fortress
Oh, that door must be the goal!
Oh, so that's what that peach was on the title and intro screens! So, I guess this means there really are no capes in this hack.
Whoa. I second-guessed myself right there. Hmm... Maybe I should press R to see what's further up ahead. (In fact, why didn't I do that earlier?)
Okay, there's a Hammer Brother platform way over there.
Ooh, bonus! I lined up the timer's ones and tens digits with the tens digit of my bonus stars completely by chance there!
Bleggh! Yeah, I wasn't about to burninate something I needed to stomp this time!
And now, the second ludicrous speed bonus game of this episode!
It's time for a disco flight!
Wow, that seemed like an unusually tricky jump.
Okay, I barely saw the next platform I'm aiming for over there.

Also, I'm sorry, but I'm not gonna be playing through the VLDC ROMs, as I'm too busy with other stuff. And, I'm not going to be resuming SMB Crossover until I finish at least either this or New Strange Mario Bros. (I'll probably finish the latter first).
Aw, nuts. I missed a coin down there that I can't be bothered to go around again to get. Now everyone's OCDs will go crazy because of this.
Talk about huge leaps. Okay, now I see a 1-up there... Ah, I think I know how to reach it...
Wow! That combo came outta nowhere!
Alright! Now, I wonder how close I am to the goal...
Hi, Yoshi!
2-life combo! Blaster combo! (9 hits)
Gulp! Well, so much for that.

Okay, now for the wall jump event. It looks like I can wall jump as many times as I want off of the same wall consecutively, which I like. And, I can combine it with the double jump. However, after doing a midair jump, I must actually land on something solid before I can do another midair jump.
Heck, yeah! There's my 1-up combo!

Well, I brought a shell. But, that's only gonna satisfy 20% of baby Yoshi's hunger, and it's too bad that I can't carry a reserve item in this hack. Hmm... Maybe I can carry Yoshi back through the pipe?
1-ups scored this time: 8.24 Bonus game average so far: 26.16 / 4 = 6.54 1-ups each.
Remove the "s" from "days".
Autoscrolling, eh? And it looks like I gotta stomp stuff to cross gaps here.
Up next is a red level, called Vile Vine. Now, I could've certainly ended the episode here, but since it's Valentine's Day, I'll go for a little extra length on today's episode.
Goal tape average so far: 336 / 11 = 30.545 stars each.
Alright, so that unlocks Rainy Clouds. And I unlocked a big yellow level named Walljump Xtrem DX * up here, and I think that * signifies something special.
Who's getting the last laugh now, message boxes? (Aww... I should've had grown-up Yoshi eat the remaining message boxes, but I didn't think to do that at the time.)
Same combo as before. No need to show the numbers in the upper-right for that combo again.
OH, YES!!! That was sweet!
Still can't see the next platform, which worries me.
Well, that's not a 50, but I'll certainly take a 40, which still helps my average.
Okay, so we've got vertical autoscrolling, with a vine that's animated to look like it's growing on layer 2, I think... And, mace cannons?!

I just wasted my double jump there. Oh, man. What have we here? Those look like those Grim Leecher enemies from Yoshi's Island: SMW2, but I think they're actually Blurps, so stomping them is out of the question.
NO WAY!!! Wow, I just scored my second 50-star hit of the day!
Wow, do I really have 93 lives right now? How many did I start the episode with? (*Goes and checks*) ...45! That means I've gained 48 lives in this episode! Holy bananas...
Whoa, hello! I just found a secret passage!
Add an "s" to "eat" here... Except, there doesn't seem to be room... Alright, see the video description for my suggestion on how to word this.
Why did I just do that? Well... Bye, Yoshi! Happy Valentine's Day!
Wow, I'm almost forced to get that 1-up combo! (I say "almost", because it looked like it was possible to skip a stomp or two, and there were 3-D glasses clouds above that I could've landed on.)
Or, be fancy and redirect the maces, though that actually appears to be of little use here.
Nuts! If it wasn't for that shell I was holding, I probably could've gotten a 1-up combo there!
Okay, let's do this right this time, and not burninate my means of getting across gaps!
Well, the music makes sense... Huh, where do I go from here?
BGM: Ievan Polkka (ASMT version)

...Pfft... Hahaha! Oh, geez! So, apparently these message boxes are actually edible, and that's how I'm supposed to make my Yoshi grow! What, do these message boxes contain chocolates? Well, it is Valentine's Day, so maybe!
OMNOMNOM!!! ...BURP! Door tastes good! The cloud was so-so. And the 3-D glasses... Bleggh!
Gulp! Good thing I didn't waste time over there! I may as well finish the level again now, since the goal's right here.
I hope I can still win the race without my peach.
Blue shell = world 2. Red shell = world 3. Which one will get a 1-up first?
There was a point there where I had to spin jump off a mace to proceed, which I bypassed last time with my athletic peach.
...That close. Anything up here? No? Aww...
There's midpoint, but the screen is still scrolling, so what's up above?
I guess that one's been munching on red koopa shells...
Made it! Wow, I'm surprised that I didn't get point-blank blasted by the mace cannons there.
Meh. I only needed 10 more stars for the bonus game anyway, and the excess stars go to waste in this hack. (Of course, getting another 50 would've been nice anyway.)
I'll just R again here...
Bah. I thought I could get more than that.
And now to go back and replay that level for the normal exit, mostly at ludicrous speed!

BGM: SMB3 - Athletic Theme
